channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: NC gubernatorial candidate Mark Robinson hires Trump-friendly lawyer to investigate porn website allegations
item.description: North Carolina Republican Mark Robinson hired attorney Jesse Binnall to lead an expeditious investigation into claims he made comments on a porn site.

item.title: Kamala Harris roasted on social media for remarks on the Book of 'Ecclesiastics'
item.description: Politicians often wind up in trouble when they start quoting from the Bible, and Kamala Harris is no exception.

item.title: You’re Wrong about Saturday Night Live
item.description: Entering its 50th year, the show is neither as good nor as bad as we remember it.

item.title: The ‘Party Of Democracy’ Successfully Kicks Two Of Its Opponents Off Georgia Ballot
item.description: The court ordered Raffensperger to place notices in polling locations warning that votes cast for West and De la Cruz will not count.

item.title: Democrat senator targeted by deepfake impersonator of Ukrainian official on Zoom call: reports
item.description: An individual impersonating the Ukrainian minister of foreign affairs reportedly contacted Democratic Sen. Benjamin Cardin this week, pressing him for foreign policy information.

item.title: California Gov. Gavin Newsom vetoes bill to help Black families reclaim taken land
item.description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom vetoed a bill Wednesday that would have helped Black families reclaim or be compensated for property that was unjustly taken by the government.

item.title: Tax-Cut Expiration Would Hurt Small Businesses
item.description: While critics of the small-business tax deduction claim that the TCJA was a tax cut exclusively for ‘millionaires and billionaires,’ the facts tell a different story.

item.title: How Lovely To See An Ad Campaign Celebrate Femininity By Using Real Women
item.description: It may be a bit of cultural flotsam but it’s not a small thing that shoemaker Stuart Weitzman’s fall 2024 ad campaign celebrates women.

item.title: Trump hits back at Harris with 'Kamala's Project 2025'
item.description: Donald Trump hit Vice President Kamala Harris with a "Project 2025" of her own on Thursday, saying she supports citizenship for "20 million illegals."

item.title: New York City Mayor Eric Adams says he won't step down after reports of indictment
item.description: New York City Mayor Eric Adams has been indicted by a grand jury on federal criminal charges, according to two people familiar with the matter, an extraordinary culmination to weeks of searches, subpoenas and resignations of top officials that have thrust the city's government into crisis.

item.title: Oregon’s ‘Rebate’ Proposal Is a Backdoor Tax Increase
item.description: It promises $1,600 to all residents. Can voters see through its fiscal façade?

item.title: The P. Diddy Indictment Is Also An Indictment Of Our Depraved Culture
item.description: For decades, Diddy made music about coercive, drug-fueled sex fantasies. Now he stands accused of living a lifestyle that matched his bravado.

item.title: Trump, Harris neck and neck in key states Arizona, Georgia, North Carolina: poll
item.description: The crucial battleground states of Arizona, Georgia and North Carolina are tossups for Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Donald Trump, a new poll says.

item.title: Georgia Supreme Court rules that votes for Cornel West, Claudia De la Cruz won't count
item.description: Presidential candidates Cornel West and Claudia De la Cruz aren't qualified to be on Georgia's ballots and votes for them should not count, the Georgia Supreme Court ruled Wednesday.

item.title: Trump and our system, &c.
item.description: On the GOP’s three-time presidential nominee; horror in Cuba, and Nicaragua; fans of Calvin Coolidge; and more.

item.title: AI Chatbots Are Programmed To Spew Democrat Gun Control Narratives
item.description: We asked AI chatbots about their thoughts on crime and gun control. As election day neared, their answers moved even further left.

item.title: Biden to sign executive order aiming to reduce gun violence, eliminate controversial gun conversion devices
item.description: President Biden is poised to sign an executive order that will address key priorities for combating firearms threats.

item.title: Harris says Trump economic plan will cause recession, says corporate taxes must increase
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris on Wednesday said former President Donald Trump's economic proposals will lead America into a recession, as she continues to pitch her economic platform to voters.

item.title: An Impressionism 150th-Birthday Bash in D.C.: C’est Magnifique
item.description: The National Gallery’s exhibition on the first Impressionist show is serious, elegant, and packed with beauties.

item.title: New ‘Dragon Age’ Video Game Indulges Trans Delusion With Avatar ‘Top Surgery Scars’ Option
item.description: The transgender character creation elements in 'Dragon Age: Veilguard' reveal the left’s pathetic obsession with self-victimization and identity politics.
